      "writtenOn": "2026-03-19T02:07:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This doesn\u0027t belong in gpio-presence.  It belongs in entity-manager itself as the probes occur.  I think someone else already has a patch for that, don\u0027t they?\n\nThe reason this doesn\u0027t belong here is because the DEVICE_NAME path is a dbus-path that is suppose to be \"private\" between the presence daemon and entity-manager and it has no correlation to a Redfish URI.  Therefore we can never add proper translation from the Argument to a valid Redfish URI.\n\nConversely, entity-manager paths usually have a corresponding Redfish URI; so we can [eventually] add valid Argument mapping in bmcweb for those dbus-path to URI translations (which are supposed to be done per the Redfish standard).",
      "revId": "d7b399cc1685b182b74f5fe4dda542c283433290",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
